The paper discusses mobile HCI and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The study also involves text entry, which could fall under the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) or Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of machine learning techniques suggests a focus on artificial intelligence, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) or Machine Learning (cs.LG).
